
Portage is a → Linux/package-managers which was originally developped for  → Linux/distributions/Gentoo, but is now also used by ChromeOS, Calculate, Sabayon and Funtoo Linux.

Because Portage is integral to Gentoo-based distributions, there's no need to install it separately on them.

